dismissalComment.html: Ashraful is gone, big blow, even though only nine balls are to go, Naeem goes for the big heave, misses, Sanga fumbles as it bounces in front of him, Ashraful wants the bye, but Sanga recovers well and hits the stumps direct to find Ashraful inches short

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Shafiul Islam 74 (73b 10x4 0x6 105m) SR: 101.36

dismissalComment.html: finally second success wicket for Bangladesh, Shafiul gets his first international wicket. It's a soft dismissal really, it's on offcutter dug in short, Sanga looks to open the face of his bat and gets an outside edge
and Dilshan goes, goes for the pull shot, is hurried into it by the skidding ball, and can't get it over midwicket where Naeem takes a nice overhead catch
Bangladesh get their first wicket, it's angled across Tharanga who goes for the big lofted shot, and is done in by the angle, getting an outside edge through to the keeper

commentTextItems.html: there it is, this time he goes back and punches this back-of-a-length delivery through covers and gets Sri Lanka home with 5.1 overs to spare

commentPostTextItems.html: Presentation for the first ODI of the decade

Kumar Sangakkara "I've seen dew before, but never like this. I wouldn't want to field in conditions like this, my bowlers wouldn't want to bowl in these conditions. The difference is, literally, day and night. Perhaps we need an 11am start, and finish the games before 6.45pm types. Talks are on, everybody has to like the idea, including the TV network." Cheeky Kumar there, but an issue certainly worth a thought in the coming six matches. Cheers
Tillkaratne Dilshan is the Man of the Match, but because of his hamstring injury he can't come out to accept the trophy.

Shakib Al Hasan "We batted really well, but the dew came in at 6pm, so it hampered us. We have four spinners, so it hurt us. Some of our middle-order batsmen didn't click today, but we are moving in the right direction."

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Chanaka Welegedara player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chanaka Welegedara player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c Welegedara b Lakmal 1 (7b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 14.28

dismissalComment.html: another one goes! Lakmal strikes again, short and wide, goes for the cut and slashes hard while doing it, flies off the outside edge and Welegedara at third man judges it superbly, running forward, diving and taking an excellent low catch

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim lbw b Randiv 35 (52b 3x4 0x6 54m) SR: 67.3

dismissalComment.html: he has given him, the sweep proves to be Rahim's downfall. He has premeditated the shot, is too far across, and fails to connect. Randiv gets him full on the toe, and the umpire has no doubts regarding this

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah lbw b Randiv 45 (47b 3x4 1x6 66m) SR: 95.74

dismissalComment.html: literally down and out as another man falls to the sweep. Decides belatedly to sweep, the ball dips and misses the bat as he falls over and is hit on the back pad in front of the stumps (down). The umpire has no choice but to lift the finger to this plumb lbw (out)

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Ashraful run out (†Sangakkara) 75 (94b 6x4 0x6 148m) SR: 79.78

dismissalComment.html: Ashraful is gone, big blow, even though only nine balls are to go, Naeem goes for the big heave, misses, Sanga fumbles as it bounces in front of him, Ashraful wants the bye, but Sanga recovers well and hits the stumps direct to find Ashraful inches short

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Rubel Hossain 14 (15b 3x4 0x6 17m) SR: 93.33

dismissalComment.html: Bangladesh get their first wicket, it's angled across Tharanga who goes for the big lofted shot, and is done in by the angle, getting an outside edge through to the keeper

headshotImage.caption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Naeem Islam b Mahmudullah 104 (122b 12x4 0x6 183m) SR: 85.24

dismissalComment.html: and Dilshan goes, goes for the pull shot, is hurried into it by the skidding ball, and can't get it over midwicket where Naeem takes a nice overhead catch

headshotImage.caption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shafiul Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Shafiul Islam 74 (73b 10x4 0x6 105m) SR: 101.36

dismissalComment.html: finally second success wicket for Bangladesh, Shafiul gets his first international wicket. It's a soft dismissal really, it's on offcutter dug in short, Sanga looks to open the face of his bat and gets an outside edge
